Peter Obi, the Vice presidential candidate in the 2019 Nigerian general election has stated that the recent approval by the Federal Executive Council FEC to spend $1.5 billion on the repairs on the Port Harcourt refinery is worrisome.  According to the former governor, Nigeria is currently on life support but those managing the country’s affairs are ”worsening it by their financial rascality.” ”The news of the planned expenditure of a whopping $1.5 billion for Port Harcourt refinery repairs is worrisome to well-meaning Nigerians. In light of our precarious economic situation, it is a huge waste. Our country on life support, but sadly the managers of our affairs are worsening the situation by their financial rascality. -PO”  Source ...Laments that Disturbing Social Happenings are Compounded, Escalated on Daily Basis by Chronic Leadership Failure of Present Governors in South East By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Southeast Based Coalition of Human Rights & Good Governance Organizations (SBCHROs) has accused Governor of Anambra State, Chief Willie Obiano of being… In "News" Lagos -  A former Governor of Anambra, Mr Peter Obi, has reiterated that investing in education will drive innovation for human capacity and economic development. Obi said this on Friday while addressing a session on the topic: ‘Innovation in Governance, a New Approach to Leadership’, at the ongoing 4th edition… In "News" By Prudence Arobani   New York   -     Nigerians in the U.S. have been tasked on the need to change their negative mindset about Nigeria and join hands and resources to help build the Nigeria of everybody’s dream. Former Governor of Anambra Peter Obi, Senators Ben Murray-Bruce and… In "News"